{
    "id": "239",
    "title": "COVID Home Safely Now (CHOSEN) Risk Score for COVID-19",
    "desc": "The COVID Home Safely Now (CHOSEN) Risk Score for COVID-19 predicts predicts suitability for discharge in COVID-19 patients.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33274414/",
                "text": "Levine DM, Lipsitz SR, Co Z, Song W, Dykes PC, Samal L. Derivation of a clinical risk score to predict 14-day occurrence of hypoxia, icu admission, and death among patients with coronavirus disease 2019. J GEN INTERN MED. Published online December 3, 2020."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [],
        "evidence": "<p>The CHOSEN Risk Score is calculated by the addition of the selected points:</p>\n<table border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 273px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Variable</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\"><strong>Points</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 84px;\" rowspan=\"4\">Age, years</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">18-45</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">46-59</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">60-73</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">&gt;73</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 84px;\" rowspan=\"4\">SpO<sub>2</sub></td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">&lt;94%</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">94-96%</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">9</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">97-98%</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">14</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">&gt;98%</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">21</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 84px;\" rowspan=\"4\">Albumin level</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">&lt;2.8 g/dL (&lt;28 g/L)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">2.8-3.3 g/dL (28-33 g/L)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">3.4-3.7 g/dL (34-37 g/L)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">15</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">&gt;3.7 g/dL (&gt;37 g/L)</td>\n<td style=\"width: 29.9567%; height: 21px;\">29</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>If albumin lab value is not available, the Modified CHOSEN Risk Score is calculated by the addition of the selected points from table below:</p>\n<table border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 273px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 426px; height: 21px;\"><strong>Variable</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\"><strong>Points</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td rowspan=\"4\" style=\"width: 213px; height: 84px;\">Age, years</td>\n<td style=\"width: 213px; height: 21px;\">18-45</td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\">12</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 213px; height: 21px;\">46-59</td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\">8</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 213px; height: 21px;\">60-73</td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\">3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 213px; height: 21px;\">&gt;73</td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td rowspan=\"4\" style=\"width: 213px; height: 84px;\">SpO<sub>2</sub></td>\n<td style=\"width: 213px; height: 21px;\">&lt;94%</td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 213px; height: 21px;\">94-96%</td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\">9</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 213px; height: 21px;\">97-98%</td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\">15</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 213px; height: 21px;\">&gt;98%</td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\">20</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td rowspan=\"4\" style=\"width: 213px; height: 84px;\">Respiratory rate, breaths per minute</td>\n<td style=\"width: 213px; height: 21px;\">&lt;18</td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\">16</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 213px; height: 21px;\">18-20</td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\">12</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 213px; height: 21px;\">21-24</td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\">5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 21px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 213px; height: 21px;\">&gt;24</td>\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 21px;\">0</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>",
        "facts": "<p>Interpretation:</p>\n<table border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 46.4639%;\"><strong>CHOSEN Score</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 46.7031%;\"><strong>Assessment for discharge*</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 46.4639%;\">0-29</td>\n<td style=\"width: 46.7031%;\">Unlikely suitable</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 46.4639%;\">30-55</td>\n<td style=\"width: 46.7031%;\">Likely suitable</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*The 30 point cutoff score showed an 83% sensitivity and 82% specificity in the original study <a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33274414/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">(Levine 2020)</a>.</p>\n<table border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 46.4639%;\"><strong>Modified CHOSEN Score</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 46.7031%;\"><strong>Assessment for discharge*</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 46.4639%;\">0-19</td>\n<td style=\"width: 46.7031%;\">Unlikely suitable</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 46.4639%;\">&gt;19</td>\n<td style=\"width: 46.7031%;\">Likely suitable</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*The 19 point cutoff score showed an 72.2% sensitivity and 73.2% specificity in the original study&nbsp;<a href=\"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33274414/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">(Levine 2020)</a>.</p>",
